# Copy to .env for local development against a real Postgres database.
# Without this file (or with it absent), the server uses local JSON-file
# storage in data/ — which is fine for home/LAN use.
#
# Neon connection string, from the Neon dashboard ("Connect" button):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@ep-xxxx-xxxx.region.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require
